Richard Paul Schifter: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 23, 2017 3:09 PM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of TPG Capital, L.P.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Richard Paul Schifter  Senior Advisor, TPG Capital, L.P.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 13 Board Members in 13 different organizations across 19 different industries.See Board Relationships64--
Background

		Mr. Richard Paul Schifter, also known as Rick, serves as Senior Advisor at Newbridge Latin America, L.P., TPG Partners I, L.P. Mr. Schifter has been a Senior Advisor at TPG Capital, L.P. since 2013. He serves as a Officer of 1996 Air G.P. Inc. He was a partner at TPG from 1994 to 2013 and its Managing Partner since July 1994. He joined at TPG Capital in 1979 and served as a Partner from 1986 to 1994. Prior to TPG, he served as a Partner of Arnold & Porter Kaye Scholer ... LLP (alternate name Arnold & Porter LLP), where he specialized in bankruptcy law and corporate restructuring from 1986 to 1994. Mr. Schifter joined TPG in 1979. Mr. Schifter serves as a Director of 1996 Air G.P. Inc. He has been an Independent Director at American Airlines Group Inc. since December 2013. He served as Independent Director of EverBank Financial Corp. from 2010 to June 9, 2017. He has been a Director of Caesars Entertainment Corporation since May 4, 2017. He serves as a Member of the Board of Overseers of the University of Pennsylvania - Law School and a Director of Youth, I.N.C. Mr. Schifter served as a Director of Midwest Air Group, Inc. since February 2008, LPL Financial Corporation since 2005 and LPL Financial Holdings Inc. since October 2005. He served as a Director of Arden Holdings Limited., Midwest Airlines, Inc., EverBank Commercial Finance, Inc., TPG Communications Inc., Mtel Latin America Inc., Controladora Milano, S.A. de C.V., Alpargatas S.A.I.C., Bristol Group SA, Grupo Milano, S.A., Direct General Corporation, Productora de Papel S.A. de C.V. (Proposa), Empresas Chocolates La Corona, S.A. de C.V. (La Corona), Republic Airways, Ecoenterprises Fund, ProSight Specialty Insurance Holdings, Inc., Gate Gourmet International and American Beacon Advisors, Inc. He served as an Independent Director of Republic Airways Holdings Inc. from July 2009 to December 16, 2013. He served as a Director of America West Holdings Corp. from 1994 to 2006. He served as a Director of Diveo Broadband Networks, Inc. He served as a Director of US Airways, LLC (formerly America West Airlines Inc.) from 1994 to November 13, 2006. He served as a Director of US Airways Group, Inc. and US Airways Inc. from September 27, 2005 to November 13, 2006. He also served as a Director of Ryanair Holdings PLC and Ryanair Limited since August 23, 1996 to 2003. He served as a Director of Endurance Specialty Insurance Ltd. and Sompo International (alternate name Endurance Specialty Holdings Ltd) from November 2004 to August 2005. Mr. Schifter received a B.A. with distinction from George Washington University in 1975 and a J.D. cum laude from the University of Pennsylvania Law School in 1978.Read Full Background




